# Project 4: Financial Performance Dashboard

## Project Overview
This project analyzes monthly financial performance using Microsoft Excel. The goal was to evaluate revenue trends, expense control, profitability, and overall business efficiency.

## Dataset Structure
The dataset includes:
- Budget Revenue
- Actual Revenue
- Revenue Variance
- Budget Expenses
- Actual Expenses
- Expense Variance
- Profit
- Profit Margin %
- Monthly Performance Classification

## Key Analysis Performed
- Revenue and Profit Trend Analysis (Pivot Tables)
- Performance Distribution (Strong / Moderate / Weak Months)
- KPI Card Creation (Total Revenue, Total Profit, Avg Margin)
- Interactive Dashboard with Charts and Slicers
- Executive Insights Summary

## Key Findings
- Total Revenue: 848,849
- Total Profit: 456,348
- 11 Strong Months, 1 Weak Month
- Highest Performance Month: November
- Strong upward revenue trend across the year

## Tools Used
- Microsoft Excel
- Pivot Tables
- Slicers
- Structured Tables
- KPI Cards
- Financial Ratio Analysis

## Conclusion
The business demonstrated strong financial health, consistent profitability, and improved performance in the final quarter of the year. Strategic focus should remain on maintaining cost efficiency during slower months.
